body:
Does verilator support constraint randomization? From the recent blog post at https://antmicro.com/blog/2023/01/open-source-systemverilog-uvm-support-in-verilator/ it seems that the crave library is integrated and should work. But I still see that verilator doesn't consider constraints during randomization. I tried testing it using the following example:

```systemverilog
class foo;

  rand bit [1:0]  num;

  constraint gen_num {
    num == 2'b00;
  }

endclass
    
// Construct the class in the TB
module foo_tb ();

  foo foo_h;

  initial begin
    foo_h = new();
    repeat (8) begin
      void'(foo_h.randomize());
      $display("%2b\n", foo_h.num);
    end

    $finish();
  end

endmodule
```

Used the following command to compile: `verilator --binary --exe --timing foo.sv`
